In this statement, President Obama sends greetings to Muslims celebrating Eid al-Fitr in the United States and around the world. He acknowledges the fasting, prayer, service, and time spent with loved ones that Muslims have dedicated to their faith during the past month. The President expresses pride in the contributions of American Muslims to democracy and the economy. He mentions the tradition of breaking fast with Muslim friends and colleagues and encourages gratitude for blessings and compassion towards those less fortunate, such as the displaced Syrians during Ramadan. The United States is providing an additional $195 million in food aid and humanitarian aid to help Syrians in need during Eid al-Fitr, bringing the total contribution to over $1 billion since the crisis began. The President concludes by wishing all Muslims a blessed and joyful celebration of Eid.